org.tensorflow.op.nn

Class SparseSoftmaxCrossEntropyWithLogits<T extends Number>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.tensorflow.op.PrimitiveOp
      • org.tensorflow.op.nn.SparseSoftmaxCrossEntropyWithLogits<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - data type for loss() output
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Op

    @Operator(group="nn")
public final class SparseSoftmaxCrossEntropyWithLogits<T extends Number>
extends PrimitiveOp
    Computes softmax cross entropy cost and gradients to backpropagate.

    Unlike `SoftmaxCrossEntropyWithLogits`, this operation does not accept a matrix of label probabilities, but rather a single label per row of features. This label is considered to have probability 1.0 for the given row.

    Inputs are the logits, not probabilities.
